---
title: Irish Sirloin Steak in Creamy Truffle Sauce with carrots and crushed baby potatoes
description: Sirloin is a favoured cut of beef for steak because of its tendency to be leaner, as well as more tender, flavourful and juicy. Here it's paired with smashed baby potatoes and a creamy truffle sauce, for an overall delightful dining experience.
