Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g} lengthways (quarter larger pieces) and pop onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer, cut-side down.

When the oven is hot, roast the potatoes on the top shelf until slightly tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Place a pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the @baby carrots{150%g} until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} and cover with a lid or foil. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from the heat and cover to keep warm.

When the potatoes have been cooking for 15 mins, remove the tray from the oven.

Use the bottom of a #bowl{} or #pan{} to gently crush each potato half.

Drizzle the smashed potatoes with a little more @oil{to taste}.

Return to the top shelf of the oven to cook until crispy and golden, ~{10-15%minutes} more.

Return the pan to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Season the @21 day aged Irish sirloin steak{250%g} with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the steaks until browned. Cook for ~{1-2%minutes} on each side for medium-rare.

Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you'd like them more well-done.

Once cooked, remove from pan, cover and allow to rest.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Return the pan to high heat, adding the @creme fraiche{110%g} and @beef stock{1%sachet}.

Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and stir through the @truffle oil{1%pack}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if required.

> Sirloin is a favoured cut of beef for steak because of its tendency to be leaner, as well as more tender, flavourful and juicy. Here it's paired with smashed baby potatoes and a creamy truffle sauce, for an overall delightful dining experience.

Thinly slice the sirloin and plate up with the creamy truffle sauce drizzled over.

Serve crushed potatoes and carrots alongside.